pr_body:
**This pull request is part of this GSoC '21 project:** https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/projects/#6101762760507392

- Closes https://github.com/godotengine/godot-proposals/issues/1253.

**Tasks completed**:

- Added button to call `GraphEdit::arrange_nodes()`
- Implemented `GraphEdit::arrange_nodes()` (*_See the proposal for reference_)
- Enabled undo/redo
- Tested in VisualScript/VisualShaders Editor
- Refactoring done

**Future work**:
- Handle edge case when no node is selected
- Minor style changes
- Add `SpinBox` for horizontal & vertical gap control


**Current Status**: Merged.

pr_title: Changes the icon of node arranger in GraphEdit & editor
pr_body:
Fixes #51680
 This PR adds new icon for Node Arrangement button in `GraphEdit` and VisualScript/VisualShader editor 

**New icon images below:**
![Screenshot (305)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41969735/129491313-4c785e3e-eca8-47c1-a391-eca0c776c454.png)
![Screenshot (304)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41969735/129491315-764ea560-b117-4f00-b925-62d560e3a6e8.png)

*Bugsquad edit:* Icon designed by @LucyLavend.

pr_title: Fixes position offset of node groups set by arrange_nodes() in GraphEdit
pr_body:
**Fixes** #51675

**Changes**: Fixed the logic to correctly set `origin`, which is used for setting position offsets of selected nodes when rearranging with `GraphEdit::arrange_nodes()`. Now the group of nodes upon rearranging won't move upwards/downwards.

**This pull request is part of this GSoC '21 project:** https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/projects/#6101762760507392

- Closes https://github.com/godotengine/godot-proposals/issues/1253.

**Tasks completed**:

- Added button to call `GraphEdit::arrange_nodes()`
- Implemented `GraphEdit::arrange_nodes()` (*_See the proposal for reference_)
- Enabled undo/redo
- Tested in VisualScript/VisualShaders Editor
- Refactoring done

**Future work**:
- Handle edge case when no node is selected
- Minor style changes
- Add `SpinBox` for horizontal & vertical gap control


**Current Status**: Merged.
